    <p>Culturelle's dominance in the probiotic category is built on a single strain: Lactobacillus rhamnosus GG (LGG) — the single most researched probiotic organism in the world with over 1,000 published clinical studies spanning three decades. LGG was the first probiotic strain to be patented (by researchers at Tufts University) and has demonstrated statistically significant benefits for antibiotic-associated diarrhea prevention, acute gastroenteritis recovery, immune function enhancement, and IBS symptom management in rigorous, placebo-controlled trials published in peer-reviewed journals.</p>

